      <h1 class="mt-5 max-w-3xl font-display text-4xl font-bold leading-tight grad-text md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">
        How Generative Engine Optimisation Works
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-200">
        <strong class="text-white">Generative search engines do not rank pages — they run a four-stage pipeline that crawls and indexes content, retrieves relevant sources, synthesises an answer with a large language model, and selects which sources to cite.</strong> Understanding every stage of that pipeline is the prerequisite for optimising it. This guide maps each stage and explains what content, structural, and entity signals determine whether your brand earns citation.
